cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about unsupervised parsing using reinforcement learning and language modeling. The most relevant sub-category is likely cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and parsing. The use of reinforcement learning and imitation learning also suggests a possible fit with cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the use of Tree-LSTM models and attention mechanisms may suggest a connection to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
